00028 /* This is a bit of a kludge for now because we're trying to use an unmodified version of the ArmDisassembler name space. */
00029 SgAsmInstruction *
00030 DisassemblerArm::disassembleOne(const MemoryMap *map, rose_addr_t start_va, AddressSet *successors)
00031 {
00032     if (start_va & 0x3)
00033         throw Exception("instruction pointer not word aligned", start_va);
00034     if (start_va >= 0xffffffff)
00035         throw Exception("instruction pointer out of range", start_va);
00036 
00037     /* The old ArmDisassembler::disassemble() function doesn't understand MemoryMap mappings. Therefore, remap the next
00038      * few bytes (enough for at least one instruction) into a temporary buffer. */
00039     unsigned char temp[4]; /* all ARM instructions are 32 bits */
00040     size_t tempsz = map->read(temp, start_va, sizeof temp, get_protection());
00041 
00042     /* Treat the bytes as a little-endian instruction. FIXME: This assumes a little-endian ARM system. */
00043     if (tempsz<4)
00044         throw Exception("short read", start_va);
00045     uint32_t c = temp[0] | (temp[1]<<8) | (temp[2]<<16) | (temp[3]<<24);
00046 
00047     /* Disassemble the instruction */
00048     startInstruction(start_va, c);
00049     SgAsmArmInstruction *insn = disassemble(); /*throws an exception on error*/
00050     ROSE_ASSERT(insn);
00051     
00052     /* Note successors if necessary */
00053     if (successors) {
00054         bool complete;
00055         AddressSet suc2 = insn->get_successors(&complete);
00056         successors->insert(suc2.begin(), suc2.end());
00057     }
00058 
00059     update_progress(insn);
00060     return insn;
00061 }

00076 SgAsmArmInstruction *
00077 DisassemblerArm::makeInstructionWithoutOperands(uint32_t address, const std::string& mnemonic, int condPos,
00078                                                 ArmInstructionKind kind, ArmInstructionCondition cond, uint32_t insn)
00079 {
00080     SgAsmArmInstruction* instruction = new SgAsmArmInstruction(address, mnemonic, kind, cond, condPos);
00081     ROSE_ASSERT (instruction);
00082 
00083     SgAsmOperandList* operands = new SgAsmOperandList();
00084     instruction->set_operandList(operands);
00085     operands->set_parent(instruction);
00086 
00087     SgUnsignedCharList bytes(4, '\0');
00088     for (int i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
00089         bytes[i] = (insn >> (8 * i)) & 0xFF; /* Force little-endian */
00090     }   
00091 
00092     instruction->set_raw_bytes(bytes);
00093

00140 SgAsmExpression *
00141 DisassemblerArm::makeRotatedImmediate() const
00142 {
00143     uint8_t rsField = (insn >> 8) & 15;
00144     uint8_t rotateCount = rsField * 2;
00145     uint32_t immRaw = insn & 0xFF;
00146     if (rotateCount == 0) {
00147         return SageBuilderAsm::makeDWordValue(immRaw);
00148     } else {
00149         return SageBuilderAsm::makeDWordValue((immRaw >> rotateCount) | (immRaw << (32 - rotateCount)));
00150     }
00151 }

00153 SgAsmExpression *
00154 DisassemblerArm::makeShifterField() const
00155 {
00156     bool i = (insn >> 25) & 1;
00157     uint8_t rsField = (insn >> 8) & 15;
00158     uint8_t rmField = insn & 15;
00159     uint8_t shiftCount = (insn >> 7) & 31;
00160     uint8_t shiftCountOr32 = shiftCount == 0 ? 32 : shiftCount;
00161     if (i) {
00162         return makeRotatedImmediate();
00163     } else if ((insn & 0xFF0) == 0) {
00164         return makeRegister(rmField);
00165     } else if ((insn & 0x070) == 0) {
00166         return SageBuilderAsm::makeLsl(makeRegister(rmField), SageBuilderAsm::makeByteValue(shiftCount));
00167     } else if ((insn & 0x0F0) == 0x010) {
00168         return SageBuilderAsm::makeLsl(makeRegister(rmField), makeRegister(rsField));
00169     } else if ((insn & 0x070) == 0x020) {
00170         return SageBuilderAsm::makeLsr(makeRegister(rmField), SageBuilderAsm::makeByteValue(shiftCountOr32));
00171     } else if ((insn & 0x0F0) == 0x030) {
00172         return SageBuilderAsm::makeLsr(makeRegister(rmField), makeRegister(rsField));
00173     } else if ((insn & 0x070) == 0x040) {
00174         return SageBuilderAsm::makeAsr(makeRegister(rmField), SageBuilderAsm::makeByteValue(shiftCountOr32));
00175     } else if ((insn & 0x0F0) == 0x050) {
00176         return SageBuilderAsm::makeAsr(makeRegister(rmField), makeRegister(rsField));
00177     } else if ((insn & 0xFF0) == 0x060) {
00178         return SageBuilderAsm::makeRrx(makeRegister(rmField));
00179     } else if ((insn & 0x070) == 0x060) {
00180         return SageBuilderAsm::makeRor(makeRegister(rmField), SageBuilderAsm::makeByteValue(shiftCount));
00181     } else if ((insn & 0x0F0) == 0x070) {
00182         return SageBuilderAsm::makeRor(makeRegister(rmField), makeRegister(rsField));
00183     } else {
00184         throw ExceptionArm("bad shifter field", this, 25);
00185     }
00186 }

00237 SgAsmDoubleWordValueExpression *
00238 DisassemblerArm::makeSplit8bitOffset() const
00239 {
00240     int32_t val = ((insn >> 4) & 0xF0) | (insn & 0xF);
00241     val <<= 24;
00242     val >>= 24; // Arithmetic shift to copy highest bit of immediate
00243     return SageBuilderAsm::makeDWordValue((uint32_t)val);
00244 }

00246 SgAsmDoubleWordValueExpression *
00247 DisassemblerArm::makeBranchTarget() const
00248 {
00249     int32_t val = insn & 0xFFFFFF;
00250     val <<= 8;
00251     val >>= 6; // Arithmetic shift to copy highest bit of immediate
00252     uint32_t targetAddr = ip + 8 + val;

00256 SgAsmExpression *
00257 DisassemblerArm::decodeMemoryAddress(SgAsmExpression* rn) const
00258 {
00259     bool bit25 = (insn >> 25) & 1;
00260     bool p = (insn >> 24) & 1;
00261     bool u = (insn >> 23) & 1;
00262     bool w = (insn >> 21) & 1;
00263     SgAsmExpression* offset = bit25 ? makeShifterField() : SageBuilderAsm::makeDWordValue(insn & 0xFFFU);
00264     switch ((p ? 4 : 0) | (u ? 2 : 0) | (w ? 1 : 0)) {
00265       case 0: return SageBuilderAsm::makeSubtractPostupdate(rn, offset);
00266       case 1: return SageBuilderAsm::makeSubtractPostupdate(rn, offset); // T suffix
00267       case 2: return SageBuilderAsm::makeAddPostupdate(rn, offset);
00268       case 3: return SageBuilderAsm::makeAddPostupdate(rn, offset); // T suffix
00269       case 4: return SageBuilderAsm::makeSubtract(rn, offset);
00270       case 5: return SageBuilderAsm::makeSubtractPreupdate(rn, offset);
00271       case 6: return SageBuilderAsm::makeAdd(rn, offset);
00272       case 7: return SageBuilderAsm::makeAddPreupdate(rn, offset);
00273       default: {
00274         ROSE_ASSERT (false);
00275         // DQ (11/29/2009): Avoid MSVC warning.
00276         return NULL;
00277       }
00278     }
00279 }

00288 SgAsmArmInstruction *
00289 DisassemblerArm::decodeMultiplyInstruction() const
00290 {
00291     SgAsmExpression* rn = makeRegister((insn >> 16) & 15);
00292     SgAsmExpression* rd = makeRegister((insn >> 12) & 15);
00293     SgAsmExpression* rs = makeRegister((insn >> 8) & 15);
00294     SgAsmExpression* rm = makeRegister(insn & 15);
00295     switch ((insn >> 20) & 15) {
00296         case 0x0: return MAKE_INSN3(mul, 3, rn, rm, rs);
00297         case 0x1: return MAKE_INSN3(muls, 3, rn, rm, rs);
00298         case 0x2: return MAKE_INSN4(mla, 3, rn, rm, rs, rd);
00299         case 0x3: return MAKE_INSN4(mlas, 3, rn, rm, rs, rd);
00300         case 0x4: return MAKE_INSN4(umaal, 3, rd, rn, rm, rs);
00301         case 0x5: throw ExceptionArm("bad bits in decodeMultiplyInstruction (0x5)", this, 20);
00302         case 0x6: throw ExceptionArm("bad bits in decodeMultiplyInstruction (0x6)", this, 20);
00303         case 0x7: throw ExceptionArm("bad bits in decodeMultiplyInstruction (0x7)", this, 20);
00304         case 0x8: return MAKE_INSN4(umull, 5, rd, rn, rm, rs);
00305         case 0x9: return MAKE_INSN4(umulls, 5, rd, rn, rm, rs);
00306         case 0xA: return MAKE_INSN4(umlal, 5, rd, rn, rm, rs);
00307         case 0xB: return MAKE_INSN4(umlals, 5, rd, rn, rm, rs);
00308         case 0xC: return MAKE_INSN4(smull, 5, rd, rn, rm, rs);
00309         case 0xD: return MAKE_INSN4(smulls, 5, rd, rn, rm, rs);
00310         case 0xE: return MAKE_INSN4(smlal, 5, rd, rn, rm, rs);
00311         case 0xF: return MAKE_INSN4(smlals, 5, rd, rn, rm, rs);
00312         default: ROSE_ASSERT (false);
00313     }
00314 // DQ (11/29/2009): Avoid MSVC warning.
00315    return NULL;

00318 SgAsmArmInstruction *
00319 DisassemblerArm::decodeExtraLoadStores() const
00320 {
00321     bool bit5 = (insn >> 5) & 1;
00322     bool bit6 = (insn >> 6) & 1;
00323     bool bit20 = (insn >> 20) & 1;
00324     bool bit21 = (insn >> 21) & 1;
00325     bool bit22 = (insn >> 22) & 1;
00326     bool bit23 = (insn >> 23) & 1;
00327     bool bit24 = (insn >> 24) & 1;
00328     SgAsmExpression* rn = makeRegister((insn >> 16) & 15);
00329     SgAsmExpression* rd = makeRegister((insn >> 12) & 15);
00330     SgAsmExpression* offset = bit22 ? (SgAsmExpression*)makeSplit8bitOffset() : makeRegister(insn & 15);
00331     SgAsmExpression* addr = NULL;
00332     switch ((bit24 ? 4 : 0) | (bit23 ? 2 : 0) | (bit21 ? 1 : 0)) {
00333         case 0: addr = SageBuilderAsm::makeSubtractPostupdate(rn, offset); break;
00334         case 1: throw ExceptionArm("bad bits in decodeExtraLoadStores (1)", this, 21);
00335         case 2: addr = SageBuilderAsm::makeAddPostupdate(rn, offset); break;
00336         case 3: throw ExceptionArm("bad bits in decodeExtraLoadStores (3)", this, 21);
00337         case 4: addr = SageBuilderAsm::makeSubtract(rn, offset); break;
00338         case 5: addr = SageBuilderAsm::makeSubtractPreupdate(rn, offset); break;
00339         case 6: addr = SageBuilderAsm::makeAdd(rn, offset); break;
00340         case 7: addr = SageBuilderAsm::makeAddPreupdate(rn, offset); break;
00341         default: ROSE_ASSERT (false);
00342     }
00343     SgAsmExpression* memref = SageBuilderAsm::makeMemoryReference(addr);
00344     uint8_t lsh = (bit20 ? 4 : 0) | (bit6 ? 2 : 0) | (bit5 ? 1 : 0);
00345     switch (lsh) {
00346         case 0:
00347             /* Should have been handled in multiply code above */
00348             throw ExceptionArm("bad bits in decodeExtraLoadStores (0)", this, 5);
00349         case 1: return MAKE_INSN2(strh, 3, rd, memref);
00350         case 2: return MAKE_INSN2(ldrd, 3, rd, memref);
00351         case 3: return MAKE_INSN2(strd, 3, rd, memref);
00352         case 4:
00353             /* Should have been handled in multiply code above */
00354             throw ExceptionArm("bad bits in decodeExtraLoadStores (4)", this, 5);
00355         case 5: return MAKE_INSN2(ldruh, 3, rd, memref);
00356         case 6: return MAKE_INSN2(ldrsb, 3, rd, memref);
00357         case 7: return MAKE_INSN2(ldrsh, 3, rd, memref);
00358         default: ROSE_ASSERT (false);
00359     }
00360 // DQ (11/29/2009): Avoid MSVC warning.
00361    return NULL;
00362 }

00364 SgAsmArmInstruction *
00365 DisassemblerArm::decodeMiscInstruction() const
00366 {
00367     bool bit7 = (insn >> 7) & 1;
00368     bool bit21 = (insn >> 21) & 1;
00369     bool bit22 = (insn >> 22) & 1;
00370     if (!bit7) {
00371       switch ((insn >> 4) & 7) {
00372         case 0: {
00373           if (bit21) {
00374             SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression* rm = makeRegister(insn & 15);
00375             bool useSPSR = bit22;
00376             uint8_t mask = (insn >> 16) & 15;
00377             SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression* psr = makePsrFields(useSPSR, mask);
00378             return MAKE_INSN2(msr, 3, psr, rm);
00379           } else {
00380             bool useSPSR = bit22;
00381             SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression* rd = makeRegister((insn >> 12) & 15);
00382             SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression* psr = makePsr(useSPSR);
00383             return MAKE_INSN2(mrs, 3, rd, psr);
00384           }
00385         }
00386         case 1: {
00387           if (bit22) {
00388             SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression* rd = makeRegister((insn >> 12) & 15);
00389             SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression* rm = makeRegister(insn & 15);
00390             return MAKE_INSN2(clz, 3, rd, rm);
00391           } else {
00392             return MAKE_INSN1(bx, 2, makeRegister(insn & 15));
00393           }
00394         }
00395         case 2: return MAKE_INSN1(bxj, 3, makeRegister(insn & 15));
00396         case 3: return MAKE_INSN1(blx, 3, makeRegister(insn & 15));
00397         case 4: throw ExceptionArm("bad bits in decodeMiscInstruction (4)", this, 4);
00398         case 5: {
00399           SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression* rd = makeRegister((insn >> 12) & 15);
00400           SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression* rn = makeRegister((insn >> 16) & 15);
00401           SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression* rm = makeRegister(insn & 15);
00402           uint8_t op = (insn >> 21) & 3;
00403           switch (op) {
00404             case 0: return MAKE_INSN3(qadd, 4, rd, rm, rn);
00405             case 1: return MAKE_INSN3(qsub, 4, rd, rm, rn);
00406             case 2: return MAKE_INSN3(qdadd, 5, rd, rm, rn);
00407             case 3: return MAKE_INSN3(qdsub, 5, rd, rm, rn);
00408             default: ROSE_ASSERT (false);
00409           }
00410         }
00411         case 6: throw ExceptionArm("bad bits in decodeMiscInstruction (6)", this, 4);
00412         case 7: {
00413           uint16_t imm1 = (insn >> 8) & 0xFFF;
00414           uint16_t imm2 = insn & 0xF;
00415           uint16_t imm = (imm1 << 4) | imm2;
00416           return MAKE_INSN1(bkpt, 4, SageBuilderAsm::makeWordValue(imm));
00417         }
00418         default: ROSE_ASSERT (false);
00419       }
00420     } else { // bit 7 set -- signed mul
00421       SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression* rd = makeRegister((insn >> 16) & 15);
00422       SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression* rn = makeRegister((insn >> 12) & 15);
00423       SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression* rs = makeRegister((insn >> 8) & 15);
00424       SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression* rm = makeRegister(insn & 15);
00425       uint8_t op = (insn >> 21) & 3;
00426       bool y = (insn >> 6) & 1;
00427       bool x = (insn >> 5) & 1;
00428       switch ((op << 2) | (x ? 2 : 0) | (y ? 1 : 0)) {
00429         case 0x0: return MAKE_INSN4(smlabb, 6, rd, rm, rs, rn);
00430         case 0x1: return MAKE_INSN4(smlabt, 6, rd, rm, rs, rn);
00431         case 0x2: return MAKE_INSN4(smlatb, 6, rd, rm, rs, rn);
00432         case 0x3: return MAKE_INSN4(smlatt, 6, rd, rm, rs, rn);
00433         case 0x4: return MAKE_INSN4(smlawb, 6, rd, rm, rs, rn);
00434         case 0x5: return MAKE_INSN4(smlawt, 6, rd, rm, rs, rn);
00435         case 0x6: return MAKE_INSN4(smluwb, 6, rd, rm, rs, rn);
00436         case 0x7: return MAKE_INSN4(smluwt, 6, rd, rm, rs, rn);
00437         case 0x8: return MAKE_INSN4(smlalbb, 7, rn, rd, rm, rs);
00438         case 0x9: return MAKE_INSN4(smlalbt, 7, rn, rd, rm, rs);
00439         case 0xA: return MAKE_INSN4(smlaltb, 7, rn, rd, rm, rs);
00440         case 0xB: return MAKE_INSN4(smlaltt, 7, rn, rd, rm, rs);
00441         case 0xC: return MAKE_INSN3(smulbb, 6, rd, rm, rs);
00442         case 0xD: return MAKE_INSN3(smulbt, 6, rd, rm, rs);
00443         case 0xE: return MAKE_INSN3(smultb, 6, rd, rm, rs);
00444         case 0xF: return MAKE_INSN3(smultt, 6, rd, rm, rs);
00445         default: ROSE_ASSERT (false);
00446       }
00447     }
00448 // DQ (11/29/2009): Avoid MSVC warning.
00449    return NULL;
00450 }

00452 SgAsmArmInstruction *
00453 DisassemblerArm::disassemble()
00454 {
00455       // fprintf(stderr, "Disassembling insn 0x%08" PRIx32 " at addr 0x%08" PRIx32 "\n", insn, p.ip);
00456       uint8_t condField = (insn >> 28) & 0xF;
00457       bool bit4 = (insn >> 4) & 1;
00458       bool bit7 = (insn >> 7) & 1;
00459       bool bit9 = (insn >> 9) & 1;
00460       bool bit16 = (insn >> 16) & 1;
00461       bool bit20 = (insn >> 20) & 1;
00462       bool bit21 = (insn >> 21) & 1;
00463       bool bit22 = (insn >> 22) & 1;
00464       bool bit23 = (insn >> 23) & 1;
00465       bool bit24 = (insn >> 24) & 1;
00466       bool bit25 = (insn >> 25) & 1;
00467       bool bit4_and_bit7 = bit4 && bit7;
00468       if (condField != 15 || !decodeUnconditionalInstructions) { // Normal instructions (or arm_cond_nv instructions if they are not treated specially)
00469         cond = (ArmInstructionCondition)(condField + 1);
00470         uint8_t dataProcOpcode = (insn >> 21) & 15;
00471         bool dpIsSpecial = (insn & 0x01900000) == 0x01000000;
00472         switch ((insn >> 26) & 3) {
00473           case 0: { // Data processing, misc, multiplies, undefined, move imm to status reg
00474             if ((insn & 0x0F0000F0U) == 0x00000090U) { // Multiplies
00475               return decodeMultiplyInstruction();
00476             } else if (bit4_and_bit7 && !bit25) {
00477               return decodeExtraLoadStores();
00478             } else if (dpIsSpecial && bit25) {
00479               if (bit21) {
00480                 SgAsmExpression* imm = makeRotatedImmediate();
00481                 bool useSPSR = bit22;
00482                 uint8_t mask = (insn >> 16) & 15;
00483                 SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression* psr = makePsrFields(useSPSR, mask);
00484                 return MAKE_INSN2(msr, 3, psr, imm);
00485               } else {
00486                   throw ExceptionArm("bad bit21", this, 26);
00487               }
00488             } else if (dpIsSpecial && !bit25) {
00489               return decodeMiscInstruction();
00490             } else { // !dpIsSpecial && !bit4_and_bit7
00491               SgAsmExpression* rn = makeRegister((insn >> 16) & 15);
00492               SgAsmExpression* rd = makeRegister((insn >> 12) & 15);
00493               SgAsmExpression* shifterField = makeShifterField();
00494               return makeDataProcInstruction(dataProcOpcode, bit20, rn, rd, shifterField);
00495             }
00496           }
00497           case 1: { // Load-store, media, undefined
00498             if (!bit4 || !bit25) {
00499               SgAsmExpression* rn = makeRegister((insn >> 16) & 15);
00500               SgAsmExpression* memref = SageBuilderAsm::makeMemoryReference(decodeMemoryAddress(rn));
00501               SgAsmExpression* rd = makeRegister((insn >> 12) & 15);
00502               bool isLoad = bit20;
00503               bool isByte = bit22;
00504               bool isTranslated = !bit24 && bit21;
00505               switch ((isTranslated ? 4 : 0) | (isLoad ? 2 : 0) | (isByte ? 1 : 0)) {
00506                 case 0: return MAKE_INSN2(str, 3, rd, memref);
00507                 case 1: return MAKE_INSN2(strb, 3, rd, memref);
00508                 case 2: return MAKE_INSN2(ldr, 3, rd, memref);
00509                 case 3: return MAKE_INSN2(ldrb, 3, rd, memref);
00510                 case 4: return MAKE_INSN2(strt, 3, rd, memref);
00511                 case 5: return MAKE_INSN2(strbt, 3, rd, memref);
00512                 case 6: return MAKE_INSN2(ldrt, 3, rd, memref);
00513                 case 7: return MAKE_INSN2(ldrbt, 3, rd, memref);
00514                 default: ROSE_ASSERT (false);
00515               }
00516             } else if ((insn & 0x0FF000F0U) == 0x07F000F0U) {
00517               return MAKE_INSN0(undefined, 9);
00518             } else {
00519               return decodeMediaInstruction();
00520             }
00521           }
00522           case 2: { // Load-store multiple, branches
00523             if (!bit25) {
00524               SgAsmExpression* rn = makeRegister((insn >> 16) & 15);
00525               SgAsmExprListExp* regs = SageBuilderAsm::makeExprListExp();
00526               for (int i = 0; i < 16; ++i) {
00527                 if ((insn >> i) & 1) {
00528                   SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression* reg = makeRegister(i);
00529                   regs->get_expressions().push_back(reg);
00530                   reg->set_parent(regs);
00531                 }
00532               }
00533               SgAsmExpression* base = rn;
00534               if (bit21) { // w
00535                 SgAsmExpression* offset = SageBuilderAsm::makeByteValue(regs->get_expressions().size() * 4);
00536                 if (bit23) { // u
00537                     base = SageBuilderAsm::makeAddPostupdate(rn, offset);
00538                 } else {
00539                     base = SageBuilderAsm::makeSubtractPostupdate(rn, offset);
00540                 }
00541               }
00542 
00543            // DQ (11/29/2009): This is a MSVC warning: warning C4805: '|' : unsafe mix of type 'uint32_t' and type 'bool' in operation
00544               switch (((insn >> 21) & 62) | bit20) { // p, u, s, l
00545                 case 0x0: return MAKE_INSN2(stmda, 3, rn, regs);
00546                 case 0x1: return MAKE_INSN2(ldmda, 3, rn, regs);
00547                 case 0x2: return MAKE_INSN2(stmda, 3, rn, SageBuilderAsm::makeArmSpecialRegisterList(regs));
00548                 case 0x3: return MAKE_INSN2(ldmda, 3, rn, SageBuilderAsm::makeArmSpecialRegisterList(regs));
00549                 case 0x4: return MAKE_INSN2(stmia, 3, rn, regs);
00550                 case 0x5: return MAKE_INSN2(ldmia, 3, rn, regs);
00551                 case 0x6: return MAKE_INSN2(stmia, 3, rn, SageBuilderAsm::makeArmSpecialRegisterList(regs));
00552                 case 0x7: return MAKE_INSN2(ldmia, 3, rn, SageBuilderAsm::makeArmSpecialRegisterList(regs));
00553                 case 0x8: return MAKE_INSN2(stmdb, 3, rn, regs);
00554                 case 0x9: return MAKE_INSN2(ldmdb, 3, rn, regs);
00555                 case 0xA: return MAKE_INSN2(stmdb, 3, rn, SageBuilderAsm::makeArmSpecialRegisterList(regs));
00556                 case 0xB: return MAKE_INSN2(ldmdb, 3, rn, SageBuilderAsm::makeArmSpecialRegisterList(regs));
00557                 case 0xC: return MAKE_INSN2(stmib, 3, rn, regs);
00558                 case 0xD: return MAKE_INSN2(ldmib, 3, rn, regs);
00559                 case 0xE: return MAKE_INSN2(stmib, 3, rn, SageBuilderAsm::makeArmSpecialRegisterList(regs));
00560                 case 0xF: return MAKE_INSN2(ldmib, 3, rn, SageBuilderAsm::makeArmSpecialRegisterList(regs));
00561                 default: ROSE_ASSERT (false);
00562               }
00563             } else {
00564               SgAsmExpression* target = makeBranchTarget();
00565               if ((insn >> 24) & 1) {
00566                 return MAKE_INSN1(bl, 2, target);
00567               } else {
00568                 return MAKE_INSN1(b, 1, target);
00569               }
00570             }
00571           }
00572           case 3: {
00573             if ((insn & 0x0F000000U) == 0x0F000000U) {
00574               return MAKE_INSN1(swi, 3, SageBuilderAsm::makeDWordValue(insn & 0x00FFFFFFU));
00575             } else {
00576                 std::cerr << "Coprocessor not supported 0x" << StringUtility::intToHex(insn) << std::endl;
00577                 throw ExceptionArm("coprocessor not supported", this, 26);
00578             }
00579           }
00580           default: ROSE_ASSERT (!"Can't happen");
00581         }
00582       } else { // Unconditional instructions
00583         cond = arm_cond_al;
00584         uint16_t opcode1 = (insn >> 20) & 0xFF;
00585 
00586      // DQ (8/30/2008): Unused value removed to avoid compiler warning.
00587      // uint16_t opcode2 = (insn >> 4) & 0xF;
00588 
00589         switch (opcode1) {
00590           case 0x10: {
00591             if (bit16) {
00592               return MAKE_INSN1(setend, 6, SageBuilderAsm::makeByteValue(bit9));
00593             } else {
00594               ROSE_ASSERT (!"CPS not supported");
00595             }
00596           }
00597           default: {
00598               std::cerr << "Cannot handle too many unconditional instructions: " << StringUtility::intToHex(insn) << std::endl;
00599               throw ExceptionArm("too many unconditional instructions", this, 32);
00600           }
00601         }
00602       }
00603 
00604    ROSE_ASSERT (!"Fell off end of disassemble");
